total_model <- brm(number~1+region*position*gender,
              data=(gender_data %>% group_by(university, department, position, gender)),
              family=poisson(link="log"),
              prior=c(prior(normal(1,2), class="b"),
                      prior(normal(1,2), class="Intercept")),
              #sample_prior = "only",
              file="total_model.RDS",
              file_refit="on_change",
              iter=4000, chains=3)
